509 { 130005, "ioctl denied due to insufficient authorisation" },
510 { 130006, "cannot read while ipfilter is disabled" },
511 { 130007, "read on minor device not supported" },
512 { 130008, "cannot write while ipfilter is disabled" },
513 { 130009, "write on minor device not supported" },
514 { 130010, "poll on minor device is not supported" },
515 { 130011, "error removing IPv4 filter hooks" },
516 { 130012, "error removing IPv6 filter hooks" },
517 { 130013, "attaching IPv4 hook failed" },
518 { 130014, "attaching IPv6 hook failed" },
519 { 130015, "ipf_init_all failed" },
520 { 130016, "finding pfil head failed" },
521 { 130017, "ipfilter is already initialised and running" },
522};
523
524
525static ipf_error_entry_t *
526find_error(errnum)
527 int errnum;
528{
529 ipf_error_entry_t *ie;
530
531 int l = -1, r = IPF_NUM_ERRORS + 1, step;
532 step = (r - l) / 2;;
533
534 while (step != 0) {
535 ie = ipf_errors + l + step;
536 if (ie->iee_number == errnum)
537 return ie;
538 step = l + step;
539 if (ie->iee_number > errnum)
540 r = step;
541 else
542 l = step;
543 step = (r - l) / 2;;
544 }
545
546 return NULL;
547}
548
549char *
550ipf_geterror(fd, func)
551 int fd;
552 ioctlfunc_t *func;
553{
554 static char text[80];
555 ipf_error_entry_t *ie;
556 int errnum;
557
558 if ((*func)(fd, SIOCIPFINTERROR, &errnum) == 0) {
559
560 ie = find_error(errnum);
561 if (ie != NULL)
562 return ie->iee_text;
563 sprintf(text, "unknown error %d", errnum);
564 } else {
565 sprintf(text, "retrieving error number failed (%d)", errno);
566 }
567 return text;
568}
569
570
571char *
572ipf_strerror(errnum)
573 int errnum;
574{
575 static char text[80];
576 ipf_error_entry_t *ie;
577
578
579 ie = find_error(errnum);
580 if (ie != NULL)
581 return ie->iee_text;
582
583 sprintf(text, "unknown error %d", errnum);
584 return text;
585}
